Program: Discovery
Title: An earth made for life - part three
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrybt
Last Broadcast Date: 15 March 2003
An exploration into earth science and the beginnings of life on the planet. The programme visits Australia to look at some of our very earliest ancestors, present in 'living rocks' and allows us to glimpse what the early earth would have looked like.